# Pad Thai

![Pad Thai](https://pixabay.com/static/uploads/photo/2016/09/26/19/06/eat-1696744_960_720.jpg)

## Ingredients

- 1 (12 ounce) package rice noodles 
- 2 tablespoons butter
- 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breast halves, cut into bite-sized pieces 
- 1/4 cup vegetable oil 
- 4 eggs
- 1 tablespoon white wine vinegar 
- 2 tablespoons fish sauce 
- 3 tablespoons white sugar
- 1/8 tablespoon crushed red pepper 
- 2 cups bean sprouts 
- 1/4 cup crushed peanuts
- 3 green onions, chopped 
- 1 lemon, cut into wedges

## Instrucions

1. Soak rice noodles in cold water 30 to 50 minutes, or until soft
2. Drain, and set aside
3. Heat butter in a wok or large heavy skillet
4. Saute chicken until browned
5. Remove, and set aside
6. Heat oil in wok over medium-high heat
7. Crack eggs into hot oil, and cook until firm
8. Stir in chicken, and cook for 5 minutes
9. Add softened noodles, vinegar, fish sauce, sugar and red pepper
10. Adjust seasonings to taste
11. Mix while cooking, until noodles are tender
12. Add bean sprouts, and mix for 3 minutes.

